One person was killed on Tuesday in a clash involving two rival groups over the control of a motorcycle/tricycle garage at Ganmo area, Ilorin, Kwara State. Our correspondent gathered that the clash was triggered by two rival groups headed by Taye Oloshe and late Albarka over the control of the motorcycle/tricycle park in the area. The leader of one of the rival groups, Albarka was killed during the clash that ensued between his group and the one headed by Taye Oloshe. A source who spoke to our correspondent on the incident said “late Albarka sustained machete cuts which led to his death”. Leader of the other rival group, Oloshe also sustained machete cuts. He is said to be at the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) of the general hospital, Oke-Oyi, Ilorin East. Confirming the incident, the spokesman of Kwara state Police Command, DSP Ajayi Okasanmi said the command has made an arrest. He explained that one person was confirmed dead while several others were injured, adding that an investigation into the cause of the crisis was going on. 3 killed as thugs clash in Ilorin Deadly cultists’ clash raises questions in Ilorin Rival cults clash in Ilorin